
TLADS Drill

Categorize each of the variables in the ESS dataset as categorical or continuous, and if continuous as ordinal, interval, 
or ratio variables.Check your work with your mentor, and discuss what that information might imply for feature engineering 
with this data.


cntry	          Country                                                                Nominal
idno            Respondent's identification number	                                   Nominal
year            ESS round	                                                             Interval
tvtot           TV watching, total time on average weekday	                           Ratio
ppltrst         Most people can be trusted or you can't be too careful	               Ratio
pplfair	        Most people try to take advantage of you, or try to be fair            Ratio
pplhlp	        Most of the time people helpful or mostly looking out for themselves   Ratio
happy	          How happy are you                                                      Ratio 
sclmeet	        How often socially meet with friends, relatives or colleagues          Ratio
sclact	        Take part in social activities compared to others of same age          Ratio
gndr	          Gender                                                                 Nominal/Ratio
agea	          Age of respondent, calculated                                          Ratio
partner         Lives with husband/wife/partner at household grid                      Nominal/Ratio

